  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>Check tender documents for completeness and update tender amendment and corrigendum</p>\n<p>Check for discrepancy and raise tender query</p>\n<p>Perform measurements and prepare Bills of Quantities</p>\n<p>Prepare and compilation for tender submission including calling of quotations, pricing, compilation of PQM, post tender questionnaires</p>\n<p>Prepare project budget and cashflow</p>\n<p>Calling of subcontract quotations, preparation of cost comparison, reports, negotiation, recommendation to award and preparation of subcontract agreement</p>\n<p>Liaise with consultants and clients for monthly progress claim and monitor against cash flow projection</p>\n<p>Evaluation of subcontractor’s claim and certification of payment</p>\n<p>Track and submit variation orders, liaise with consultants for assessment</p>\n<p>Liaise and negotiate with consultants and client for finalization of accounts</p>\n<p>Any ad-hoc duties assigned by the Contract Manager &amp; management.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>Degree/ Diploma in Building/ Quantity Surveying</p>\n<p>3 years relevant experience</p>\n<p>Able to work independently</p>\n<p>Team player with Positive learning and Positive working attitude</p>\n<p>Able to work under tight deadline with less supervision</p>",
